name: websocket2webhook
description: ###Introduction### This is an example of subscribing to the [Eagle Eye Video API](https://een.com) in order to monitor status of cameras and bridges.  This example uses [websocket polling](https://apidocs.eagleeyenetworks.com/apidocs/#websocket-polling).  It will look for events the user cares about and store them inside of a queue.  The workers pull items off the queue and send them as webhooks.
author: mcotton@een.com
